FBIS3-55430 "drsov006_g_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Army To Be Reduced to 100,000 in 1994 LD0801210594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 8 Jan 94 LD0801210594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The second stage of reform in the Belarusian Armed Forces will be completed in 1994. According to reports from the republic, the strength of the Belarusian Army will be reduced to 100,000 men. This is three times less than the strength of the military grouping inherited from the former Soviet Union. According to the Belarusian defense doctrine law, the strength of the national army should be within the limits needed to ensure the country's sovereignty.
